---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="CV" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Curriculum Vitae</div>
    <p class="py-2 opacity-80">
      Education, research, teaching, and technical background.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="divider my-2"></div>

  <!-- Profile -->
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    PhD researcher in Business Analytics and Operations Management at Sabanci Business
    School, with a background in industrial engineering. My research develops mathematical
    models for operational decision-making under uncertainty — combining robust optimization,
    stochastic programming, and integer programming to build plans that remain feasible and
    near-optimal when realized conditions deviate from expectations. Application domains
    include healthcare operations, sustainable supply chains, and remanufacturing systems. I
    am particularly interested in problems where the coupling of multiple resource types
    under uncertainty creates challenges that decomposition-based or uncertainty-aware
    formulations are uniquely positioned to address.
  </div>

  <!-- Education -->
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>
  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="PhD — Business Analytics & Operations Management"
      subtitle="Sep 2024 — Present · Sabanci Business School, Sabanci University · Istanbul, Türkiye · GPA 3.5 / 4.00 · Full Scholarship"
    >
      <strong>Coursework:</strong> Modelling in Operations Management · Stochastic
      Processes · Data Mining · Operations and Decision Analytics · Empirical Methods in
      Operations Management · Data and AI Ethics · Philosophy of Science and Society ·
      Judgment and Decision Making · Probability and Statistics · Operations Research.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="MSc — Industrial Engineering"
      subtitle="Sep 2018 — Sep 2021 · Iran University of Science and Technology · Tehran, Iran · GPA 18.33 / 20.00 · Fellowship recipient"
    >
      <strong>Thesis:</strong> Multi-objective robust optimization model for hybrid
      manufacturing and remanufacturing under simultaneous uncertainty in return quality,
      processing times, and demand. Supervisor: Dr. Ahmad Makui.<br />
      <strong>Coursework:</strong> Game Theory · Econometrics · Operations Research ·
      Robust Optimization · Fuzzy Theory and Applications · Network Theory · Systems
      Engineering · Computer Simulation and Optimization.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="BSc — Industrial Engineering"
      subtitle="Sep 2013 — Sep 2017 · Amirkabir University of Technology · Tehran, Iran · Fellowship recipient · Top 2% in Iran's University Entrance Exam"
    >
      <strong>Thesis:</strong> Statistical risk assessment in mine operations. Supervisor:
      Dr. Kourosh Shahriar.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <!-- Working Papers -->
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Working Papers</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-10 grid gap-4">
    <a href="/projects/msc-thesis--multi-objective-robust-optimization-for-remanufacturing-systems"
      class="block rounded-xl border border-base-300 hover:border-base-content/20 hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-[2px] transition-all duration-200 ease-out p-5">
      <p class="font-semibold leading-snug">
        Multi-objective robust optimization for hybrid manufacturing and remanufacturing
        planning under simultaneous uncertainty in return quality, processing times, and demand.
      </p>
      <div class="text-sm opacity-60 mt-1">
        H. Rahmani, A. Makui — <em>Working paper · In progress</em>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mt-3 text-sm font-medium opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-150">
        <span class="badge badge-secondary text-xs">Working Paper</span>
        Read more about this paper →
      </div>
    </a>
    <a href="/projects/tire-closed-loop-supply-chain-network-design-under-uncertainty"
      class="block rounded-xl border border-base-300 hover:border-base-content/20 hover:shadow-md hover:-translate-y-[2px] transition-all duration-200 ease-out p-5">
      <p class="font-semibold leading-snug">
        Sustainable closed-loop supply chain network design for remanufacturing under
        hybrid uncertainty — a robust fuzzy stochastic programming approach.
      </p>
      <div class="text-sm opacity-60 mt-1">
        H. Rahmani, A. Makui — <em>Working paper · In progress</em>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mt-3 text-sm font-medium opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-150">
        <span class="badge badge-secondary text-xs">Working Paper</span>
        Read more about this paper →
      </div>
    </a>
  </div>

  <!-- Research Experience -->
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Research Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 mt-2 opacity-80">Sabanci University</div>
  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-8">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Robust Optimization for Integrated Healthcare Scheduling"
      subtitle="Jan 2026 · Sabanci Business School · Supervisor: Dr. Burak Gökgür"
    >
      Formulated a multi-resource MILP with budgeted uncertainty sets (Bertsimas & Sim) in
      Python and Gurobi to jointly optimize surgical case planning and nurse-to-patient
      assignment. Quantified the Price of Robustness across a Γ sweep, demonstrating that
      modest conservatism eliminates nurse workload violations during demand spikes with
      minimal throughput cost.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="The Integrated Healthcare Timetabling Problem — A Systematic Review"
      subtitle="Oct 2025 · Sabanci Business School · PhD Summer Paper · Supervisor: Dr. Can Akkan"
    >
      Synthesized 50+ papers on Patient Admission Scheduling, Surgical Case Planning, and
      Nurse-to-Room Assignment, tracing the field from foundational metaheuristics to modern
      robust and stochastic formulations. Developed an integration taxonomy and identified
      the open gap between fully integrated models and uncertainty-aware planning.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Next-Basket Prediction using Bidirectional Transformers"
      subtitle="Jun 2025 · Sabanci Business School · Supervisor: Dr. Yücel Saygın"
    >
      Developed a progressive enhancement framework for e-commerce recommendation,
      replacing a GRU baseline with a BERT4Rec bidirectional Transformer and structured
      data augmentation. Achieved a 4× improvement in Recall@10 on the Retail Rocket
      dataset; isolated the contribution of architecture versus augmentation through
      controlled ablation.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Proactive Environmental Strategies and Supply Chain Performance"
      subtitle="Jun 2025 · Sabanci Business School · Supervisor: Dr. Melek Akın Ateş"
    >
      Applied PLS-SEM (SmartPLS) to survey data from Turkish manufacturing firms to test
      how customer pressure and organizational commitment drive proactive environmental
      strategies, and how those strategies mediate the path to environmental investment
      outcomes. Full mediation confirmed across both antecedents.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Customer Lifetime Value Assessment via Weighted K-Means Clustering"
      subtitle="Jan 2025 · Sabanci Business School · Supervisor: Dr. Kemal Kılıç"
    >
      Integrated RFM behavioral scoring with CLV-weighted K-Means clustering on a
      2,239-customer grocery dataset. CLV weighting produced tighter, better-separated
      segments (lower SSE, higher Silhouette Score) and correctly split the Loyal Customers
      group by future value — a distinction invisible to standard RFM classification.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 opacity-80">Iran University of Science and Technology</div>
  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="MSc Thesis — Multi-objective Robust Optimization for Remanufacturing Systems"
      subtitle="Sep 2021 · School of Industrial Engineering · Supervisor: Dr. Ahmad Makui"
    >
      Developed and solved a multi-period, multi-objective robust MILP for hybrid
      manufacturing and remanufacturing planning under simultaneous uncertainty in return
      quality, processing times, and demand. NSGA-II outperformed MOPSO across all
      Pareto-frontier quality metrics. Validated on an industrial case study, achieving a
      14% reduction in total cost and 10% reduction in environmental impact relative to the
      deterministic baseline.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Blockchain-Based Verification Frameworks for Supply Chain Transparency"
      subtitle="Jan 2023 · School of Industrial Engineering · Supervisor: Dr. Morteza Ghomi-Avili"
    >
      Analysed a blockchain-enabled closed-loop supply chain framework combining IoT/RFID
      traceability, smart contract governance, and multi-objective fuzzy network
      optimization. Examined how tamper-evident ledgers convert sustainability commitments
      into auditable, self-executing supply chain governance.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Large-Scale Optimization of Healthcare Logistics via Benders Decomposition"
      subtitle="Dec 2019 · School of Industrial Engineering · Supervisor: Dr. Hadi Sahebi"
    >
      Implemented a Benders decomposition scheme in GAMS for blood supply chain network
      design — master problem on strategic facility decisions, subproblem on operational
      flows subject to perishability and stochastic demand. Cut management achieved
      near-optimal solutions at a fraction of the monolithic MILP solve time.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Review of Data-Driven Robust Optimization Methodologies"
      subtitle="Dec 2019 · School of Industrial Engineering · Supervisor: Dr. Mir Saman Pishvaee"
    >
      Surveyed major data-driven robust optimization frameworks — including uncertainty set
      construction from empirical data, distributionally robust approaches, and
      sample-average approximation — and evaluated their applicability to supply chain and
      production planning problems.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Analytical Approaches in Multi-Modal Transportation Systems"
      subtitle="Jun 2019 · School of Industrial Engineering · Supervisor: Dr. Mahdi Hosseini-Motlagh"
    >
      Reviewed optimization and analytical methods for multi-modal transportation planning,
      examining trade-offs between cost, service level, and environmental impact in
      integrated freight and logistics networks.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Discrete-Event Simulation for Transportation System Performance Analysis"
      subtitle="Jan 2019 · School of Industrial Engineering · Supervisor: Dr. Kamran Shahanaghi"
    >
      Built an Arena discrete-event simulation of a multi-stage transportation system,
      generating utilization profiles, queue-length distributions, and throughput sensitivity
      curves. Identified that the binding bottleneck was the stage with the highest
      utilization–variance product, not the highest mean utilization — a finding invisible
      to deterministic network models.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <!-- Teaching -->
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Teaching Experience</div>
  </div>
  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Graduate Teaching Assistant — Sabanci Business School"
